<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,866]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,769,794]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The shape of the cerci with their distinctive basal lobes and the distinctive vase shaped phallus serve to easily distinguish this species from other species in the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1232,841,866]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,866]" box="[199,1232,841,866]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,841,866]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the presence of additional basal lobes on the cerci.
</paragraph>
